BOJ Governor Shirakawa’s Salary Was Double Bernanke’s in 2010

-- B y   L i l y   N o n o m i y a
-- 
2011-06-30T09:23:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/boj-governor-shirakawa-s-salary-was-double-bernanke-s-in-2010.html
Bank of Japan Governor Masaaki Shirakawa earned about $427,900 last year, more than double that
of Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke .  Shirakawa made 34.396 million yen in the fiscal year ended
March 2011, the central bank said in a  statement  in  Tokyo  today.
Bernanke made $199,700 in 2010.  Shirakawa’s salary is still lower than that of European
Central Bank President Jean-Claude Trichet, who earned 367,863
euros ($532,959) and Hong Kong Monetary Authority Chief
Executive Norman Chan, who got paid HK$7.5 million ($964,000)
plus HK$868,000 in benefits.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lily Nonomiya in Tokyo at 
